fields.description:
Sign up user with fields defined in the settings.

    If the email field of the user model is part of the
    registration fields (default), check if there is
    no user with that email or as a secondary email.

    If it exists, it does not register the user,
    even if the email field is not defined as unique
    (default of the default django user model).

    When creating the user, it also creates a `UserStatus`
    related to that user, making it possible to track
    if the user is archived, verified and has a secondary
    email.

    Send account verification email (setting value).

    If allowed to not verify users login, return token.
fields.name: signUp

fields.description:
Send password reset email.

    For non verified users, send an activation email instead.

    If there is no user with the requested email, a successful response
    is returned.
fields.name: sendPasswordResetEmail

fields.description:
Change user password without old password.

    Receive the token that was sent by email.

    If token and new passwords are valid, update user password and in
    case of using refresh tokens, revoke all of them.

    Also, if user has not been verified yet, verify it.
fields.name: passwordReset

fields.description:
Change account password when user knows the old password.

    A new token and refresh token are sent. User must be verified.
fields.name: passwordChange

fields.description:
Archive account and revoke refresh tokens.

    User must be verified and confirm password.
fields.name: archiveAccount

fields.description:
Delete account permanently or make `user.is_active=False`.

    The behavior is defined on settings. Anyway user refresh tokens are
    revoked.

    User must be verified and confirm password.
fields.name: deleteAccount

fields.description:
Update the account settings of the authenticated user
    such as their first and last name.

    A verified account is required.
fields.name: updateAccount

fields.description:
Update the role of an existing user.

    A Supervisor role is required for the caller.

    The specified user needs to be in the same
    organization of the caller.
fields.name: updateTeamMemberRole

fields.description:
Create a new invitation object.

    Send invitation email to the invited email address.

    If there is no user with the requested email,
    a successful response is returned.
fields.name: inviteMember

fields.description:
Remove an existing user in the organization.

    A Supervisor role is required for the caller.

    The specified user needs to be in the same
    organization of the caller.
fields.name: removeTeamMember

fields.description:
Obtain JSON web token for given user.

    Allow to perform login with different fields, The fields are defined
    on settings.

    Not verified users can log in by default. This can be changes on
    settings.

    If user is archived, make it unarchived and return
    `unarchiving=True` on OutputBase.
fields.name: tokenAuth

fields.description:
### Checks if a token is not expired and correct.

    *Note that this is not for refresh tokens.*
fields.name: verifyToken

fields.description:
### refreshToken to generate a new login token:

    *Use this only if `JWT_LONG_RUNNING_REFRESH_TOKEN` is True*

    using the refresh-token you already got during authorization, and
    obtain a brand-new token (and possibly a new refresh token if you
    revoked the previous). This is an alternative to log in when your
    token expired.
fields.name: refreshToken

fields.description:
### Suspends a refresh token.

    *token must exist to be revoked.*
fields.name: revokeToken

fields.description:
Create a new campaign

    #### Args Ex:

    name: "test 1"

    uniqueId: "test-1-campaign"
    **only lowercase [a-z], digits, and hyphens**

    targetUrl: "https://asl19.org"
    **https only**

    planType: "1"
    **ONE-TIME (1) or MONTHLY (2)**

    source: "beepass"

    medium: "vpn"

    regionsList: "mena, iran"

    startDate: "2021-01-22"
    **YYY-MM-DD date format**

    impressionPerPeriod: 20000
fields.name: createCampaign

fields.description:
Duplicate an existing campaign by its uniqueId.

    The uniqueId of the new campaign will be the same as the
    original one suffixed with `.copy{count}`, e.g. copy1
fields.name: duplicateCampaign

fields.description:
Remove an existing campaign by its uniqueId.

    This will enable the `removed` boolean of the campaign and will not actually delete
    the campaign object itself.
fields.name: deleteCampaign

fields.description:
Enable (activate) a campaign by its uniqueId.

    The campaign to be enabled has to be approved and disabled.
    Pending, expired, removed, or draft campaigns cannot be enabled nor disabled.
fields.name: enableCampaign

fields.description:
Disable (pause) a campaign by its uniqueId.

    The campaign to be disabled has to be approved and enabled.
    Pending, expired, removed, or draft campaigns cannot be enabled nor disabled.
fields.name: disableCampaign

types.name: __Schema

types.description:
The fundamental unit of any GraphQL Schema is the type. There are many kinds of types in GraphQL as represented by the `__TypeKind` enum.

Depending on the kind of a type, certain fields describe information about that type. Scalar types provide no information beyond a name, description and optional `specifiedByURL`, while Enum types provide their values. Object and Interface types provide the fields they describe. Abstract types, Union and Interface, provide the Object types possible at runtime. List and NonNull types compose other types.
types.name: __Type

enumValues.name: OBJECT

enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an interface. `fields`, `interfaces`, and `possibleTypes` are valid fields.
enumValues.name: INTERFACE

enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a union. `possibleTypes` is a valid field.
enumValues.name: UNION

enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an enum. `enumValues` is a valid field.
enumValues.name: ENUM

enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an input object. `inputFields` is a valid field.
enumValues.name: INPUT_OBJECT

enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a list. `ofType` is a valid field.
enumValues.name: LIST

enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a non-null. `ofType` is a valid field.

types.description:
A Directive provides a way to describe alternate runtime execution and type validation behavior in a GraphQL document.

In some cases, you need to provide options to alter GraphQL's execution behavior in ways field arguments will not suffice, such as conditionally including or skipping a field. Directives provide this by describing additional information to the executor.
